sentences.content: The following exercises allow me to fill in the prompts given the corresponding response lists in increasingly more difficult ordering until no response list is shown.
A daisy is a kind of [_flower_].
A baby sheep is a [_lamb_].
You write on a blackboard with [_chalk_].
A group of birds is called a [_flock_].
A train rides on [_rails_].
A baby cow is called a [_calf_].
A college teacher is a [_professor_].
A person who serves on a ship is a [_sailor_].
An animal that produces wool is a [_sheep_].
Soap for washing hair is called [_shampoo_].
A place to pray is called a [_church_].
A cover for a wound is a [_bandage_].
An insect that makes honey is a [_bee_].
A person who waits tables is a [_server_].
The limb of a tree is a [_branch_].
A stick of wax that burns is a [_candle_].
A group of cattle is a [_herd_].
Hair on a man's face are called [_whiskers_].
A gem from an oyster is a [_pearl_].
You chew food with your [_teeth_].
A shape with three sides in a [_triangle_].
A grown person is an [_adult_].
Airplanes land at the [_airport_].
After asking a question, you expect an [_answer_].
The air around the earth is its [_atmosphere_].
A professional who cuts hair is a [_barber_].
The Christian holy book is the [_Bible_].
Jewelry worn on the wrist is called a [_bracelet_].
